edu.ncsu.csc216.airport_customs.simulation

Class EventCalendar

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.airport_customs.simulation.EventCalendar

  • public class EventCalendar
extends java.lang.Object
    A calendar that determines the order in which passengers leave their queues. The arrival hall is a queue, as are the wait lines at customs desks. An event corresponds to passenger leaving their queue.
    Version:
    3.0
    Author:
    Jo Perry

    • Method Detail

      • nextToBeProcessed

        public TransitSystem nextToBeProcessed()
        Determines which customs desk or if arrival hall contains the next passenger to be processed. With a tie, the desk with the smallest index wins. If the tie is with the arrival hall, the arrival hall wins.
        Returns:
        The line whose front passenger has the earliest departure time.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if all lines are empty.
